> The Meyer lemon is a hybrid citrus fruit - taking both the refreshing and tangy character
> of the lemon, and the sweet flavor of the orange. It's the perfect match for the
> Spring flavors in this risotto!

== Risotto and Stock ==

In a small #pot, bring @water{4%cups} to a simmer with the @veggie stock concentrate{1}
over medium-low heat. Trim and discard bottom 1 inch of the @asparagus{1%bunch}, then
cut into 1-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and finely chop the @yellow onion{1}. Finely mince
or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. Finely chop the @parsley{1%bunch}. Zest and halve the
@Meyer lemon{1}.

Heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a large #pan over the medium heat. Add the onion to
the pan and cook, stirring, for ~{5%minutes}, until softened. Add half the garlic and
cook for another ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the @Arborio rice{3/4%cup} to the onion mixture and stir to coat.

> Hint: If you have some white wine handy, this would be the great time to add a splash!
> Just let it bubble until nearly evaporated. Otherwise, begin adding the stock to the
> pan, 1/2 cup at a time, stirring between each addition, until liquid is absorbed.
> Continue adding stock by the 1/2-cupfull until the rice is tender with some bite to it,
> about 30 minutes.

Start adding stock to the pan, 1/2 cup at a time, stirring between each addition,
until liquid is absorbed. Continue adding stock by the 1/2-cupfull until the rice is
tender with some bite to it, about ~{30%minutes}.

== Asparagus and Shrimp ==

In between additions, heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in another medium #pan over
medium heat. Add the asparagus and cook, tossing, for about ~{3%minutes}. Add the
@shrimp{10%ounce} and the remaining garlic and cook, tossing, until shrimp is just pink
and asparagus is crisp-tender. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and set aside.

== Assembly ==

When the risotto is al dente, stir in the shrimp, asparagus, @butter{1%tablespoon},
the lemon zest, half the parsley, and half the @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{} and a squeeze of Meyer lemon.

Sprinkle the risotto with the remaining Parmesan and parsley and enjoy!